DialogText: It handles taking the extracted ore to ore processing, and then stores the output inside the network. This network is overkill, but it's the kind of nonsense I have to do to impress the nukes. The controller is the brain and has nerves coming off on all sides. They are color-coded so they don't accidentally connect to each other.Each side has a job:Left: Ore extractionRight: Ore processingBottom: Love and care of the reactorsFront: ConsolesThe top and back aren't doing anything . . . yet. In a normal lab, one would probably handle autocrafting, and another a bank of other various machines.
